notesStmt.note: Camillo Jaghel: inscribed with his name, 1619 (folio 231v); see William Popper, The Censorship of Hebrew Books (New York: KTAV Publishing House, 1969), appendix § 50-56.
Owner's inscription in Italian, partially illegible: 'Questo lib[ro] .. David a Samuel .. Moise Borghi (?) (folio 1r).
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 38; written lines: 38; Uniform layout. Visible hard-point ruling. Initial words written in larger characters. Hair side and flesh side are indistinguishable. Erasures presumably by the censor (e. g. folios 15r, 116v, 224v, 227r). Unfoliated blank leaf after folios 105, 208.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Italian square script of the 15th century, punctuated. Micha᾿el (?): the name Michael is decorated (folio 168r).

binding.p: Pre-1600. Brown leather, gold tooled, with remains of clasps. Spine: 'Machazor. Ritus Italici. Hebraice. Mus. Brit. Jure Emptionis 19,064.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Adolphus Asher (b. 1800, d. 1853), Berlin bookseller and dealer to the British Museum (see 131-153: inscribed, [232v].
